<br>
Our punishment:  Banning from posting raids on this calandar for one month, even though 90% of the community thought that we should have had the rules bent for us.  At that time, I was a little pissed at the decision, however we lived with it knowing that at that point and time, we WERE in the wrong.<br>
<br>
My point is this.  Be it a small rule, or a large rule, if you break them, then you should be held responsible for it.  Don't get me wrong, I know quite a few people that are in SoT, some in RL, and hell they are great people, but as the saying goes; If you wanna play in the game, you have to abide by the rules.<br>
<br>
I'm actually a rather new member to Tindi, however I'm starting to get a hang of the &quot;high end&quot; game now that I am.  I think that the same rules that apply LoM, EotF, etc etc (examples only) should apply to everyone.  You may say that the rules don't apply due to them not being on the rotation, however if you look instead at the spirit of rules rather than the exact rule itself, I think you'll agree.<br>
<br>
Anyways, just my two bits here.. hope this can be worked out. <p><CENTER>
