<br>
You get your day. <br>
<br>
And you get a privilege : The server promises to leave you alone with the mob on rotation that day. No one will interfere, no one will try to race and kill.<br>
<br>
<br>
You also make a commitement : You will do your upmost to kill that mob within your time frame and if you fail no one will be pissed, @#%$ happens.<br>
<br>
<br>
What happened here is a guild had a few rotations up (luck of the draw).<br>
Not impossible to do thanks to their power but hard nevertheless because of their &quot;short&quot; window of effectiveness (timewise).<br>
This guild decided to kill OTHER mobs than those on rotation and also refused to discuss or solve their problem of respecting the rotation.<br>
<br>
We all understand the concept of real Life and work and familly.<br>
Had this guild gone directly for the rotation mobs and have had to overstepped the 24h limit would they have been aggressed by the other members of the community ?<br>
<br>
<br>
Most surely NOT.<br>
<br>
I do hope you are honest enough to realise this as the truth.<br>
<br>
