See, here is where you are missing the whole point of the flame board my dear anonymoid.  Folks tend to be on their best behavior when the teacher is in the room, or a cop walks by.  Why is that?  Because these people have the power to punish transgressions.  Similarly, the flame board is EQ's 'cop' because it also gives members the power to punish transgressions through social ostracism, flames and laughter directed at the transgressors.<br>
<br>
It's funny that this has to be spelled out three years into this game really.  Everyone knows the flames and flame boards serve an important purpose since there is basically no other way to police intentionally inappropriate or disrespectful behavior in this game.  However, the impact of flame boards upon transgressors is only as effective as the level of 'care' such people have at being ostracized and laughed at.  The more that members of SoT respond to flames and thus exhibit a high level of care, the more obvious it is that the flame board is an effective way to police their conduct.<br>
<br>
That, after all, is what makes every SoT post herein claiming otherwise, a joke unto itself.<br>
