<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;This seems a big deal to me when one guild has an overcrowded day of mobs, chooses to add more, then takes the next day to kill ones they were supposed to the first&quot; -- Wadce</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
  I agree, it's also a sign of greed.  Hogging all the &quot;uber&quot; mobs to get as much loot as possible, without giving any regard to the time limitation that was specified.  It's like putting too much on your plate and trying to eat it all.  And now, because of that, the community has a stomach ache. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
  Another thing.  When asked if your guild is going to take their turn on a rotation mob, a Guild Leader should definitely answer to the best of his or her ability.  By not answering, guilds like BotS in this case are left twiddling their thumbs waiting patiently on the edge of their seats ready to piss their pants in excitement while they wait on you hand-and-foot in hopes you'll give them a straight answer on what mob you're killing (and when you are going to in fact kill it)!  Just to reiterate, not answering is lame and just plain rude.  People don't play this game to sit around deciding what mobs you want to kill.  Contrary to any other belief's, the world does not revolve around you and the rest of the Rathe doesn't cater to your needs.<br>
<br>
  SoT did something wrong and are now being slapped on the wrists for it.  Merloc posted an honest issue he had with the breaking of a rotation.  He did not slander SoT, but instead proposed how to penalize them and even called for outside opinions.  What was he met with?  Whiners, flamers, sarcasm, and attitude.  Instead of getting all up in arms about the situation, SoT should realize that they need to be penalized for breaking the 24 hour time allotment.  If it goes neglected and falls by the wayside, then other guilds will might assume: &quot;Oh we can push this mob past 24hrs, I remember when SoT did it on KT and they got away with it..&quot;<br>
<br>
  Ignoring the breaking of the 24hr time allotment does not make the issue go away and sets a bad example for the rest of the guilds on the rotation, those soon to be on the rotation, and those that one day WILL be on the rotation.  <br>
<br>
  Solutions are found by confronting the problem and that is exactly what Merloc did.  Put down your wooden spoon's, back away slowly, and I promise you everything will be okay.<br>
